# Testing Standards

Coverage requirements:
- New business logic requires unit tests
- All new endpoints require integration tests
- Tests must be colocated in the feature or module `tests/` subfolder

Test placement:
- Unit tests → `frontend/src/features/<feature>/tests/` or `backend/app/modules/<module>/tests/`
- Integration/e2e tests spanning multiple modules → root `tests/` folder only
- Never dump all tests into a single top-level folder

Backend:
- Use pytest with async support for FastAPI endpoints
- Mock external services at the repository or HTTP client boundary
- Test service.py business logic in isolation from DB when practical
- Integration tests use a test database — never production

Frontend:
- Use React Testing Library for component tests
- Test hooks independently where business logic lives
- Mock API calls at the api/ layer, not inside components
- Do not test implementation details — test user-visible behavior

General:
- Tests must be deterministic — no flaky time or random dependencies
- One logical assertion focus per test; descriptive test names
- No skipped tests without a linked issue and justification
